# 8. わたし達の映画

Akito: It's finally the day...
An: Yeah. Also, I can't wait to see what the other classes are gonna do.
An: And we get to vote on which did the best, right? How awesome would it be to win first prize?!
Nene: F-First might be kinda tough... I heard the other classes also put a lot of effort into their things.
Mizuki: Hey, you guys!
Nene: Oh... Hi, Akiyama, Aoyagi...
An: Your class is performing a dance routine, right? Don't you guys need to change? Do you still have time?
Mizuki: Yup! When we drew straws to see who's gonna go first, our class ended up somewhere towards the end!
Toya: Your class made a film, right? How'd it turn out...?
Akito: Just fine. Shooting it wasn't easy, but all that's left for us is to have everyone watch it.
Nene: I dunno if I'm gonna be nervous or excited when it plays.
Toya: Does that mean the shoot went well...?
Nene: It did. And the books you found for me really helped a lot, Aoyagi.
Nene: Sorry I couldn't thank you sooner. But I really appreciate what you did for me...
Mizuki: While we're on the subject, Li'l Bro, you're the star, right? I can't wait to see how you did.
Akito: Just sit and watch quietly for me, will you?
MC: The opening ceremony for the first annual Kamiyama High School Arts Festival will now begin. We ask that you all please take your seats.
An: Oh, it's starting! Let's go rejoin our class!
Mizuki: See you later, guys! It's the first ever arts festival, so let's make it a fun one♪
Nene: (Everyone's gonna see our film soon...)
Nene: (It doesn't screen for a while, but my heart's already pounding... I'm not sure it's gonna make it through the whole thing...)
Rui: “Thank you all for watching...”
Tsukasa: “Thank you very much!!!”
An: That was a great play! Kamishiro's class did such a good job!
Akito: But it sorta didn't make any sense... What happened to paying homage to “The Phantom Of The Opera”...?
Nene: I wouldn't have guessed there'd be a passage to another world hidden underground, or that they'd fight a dragon there... It is something they'd come up with, though.
Nene: (They did put on a really good performance, but I couldn't focus on it towards the end...)
Nene: (Because... Next...)
MC: That concludes Class 3-C's play. Next, we have a film by Class 2-A.
MC: Our screening of “The Wandering Cook: A Post-Apocalyptic Tale of Gourmet Martial Arts” will now begin.
Nene: This is it...
An: Yeah... I'm so nervous... My face is gonna be on that screen.
Akito: It's way too late to be saying anything like that.
An: Look who's talking. You seem pretty tense. I bet you're just as nervous.
Akito: Quiet...
Nene: (These two get nervous about stuff?)
Nene: (I really got to see a new side of everyone through this festival...)
An: Oh, it's starting...!
Narrator: “Far in the future... A series of disasters has led humanity to the brink of extinction...”
Girl: “Huff... Huff... I'm almost home...”
Wandering Cook: “I'm just a humble cook...”
Mizuki: Hey, An and Li'l Bro are both doing a pretty good job!
Toya: Yes, they are...
Wandering Cook: “I'm a cook... My purpose in life is to make the best food I can for those who need it...”
Wandering Cook: “I don't care how hard it's going to be for me to do that. I'm not giving up...!”
Tsukasa: Well now... Those are some very convincing stunts.
Rui: They must've practiced quite a lot.
Girl: “No, Mr. Cook, where are you going...?!”
Girl: “Please stay...! I want you to stay in this village forever and ever!”
Former Dark Cook A: “Yeah, boss! You even helped us change our ways! After we attacked you, we became so hungry that we couldn't move... But then you made food for us...”
Former Dark Cook B: “You also reminded us of the importance of wanting to serve people the best food possible regardless of who comes asking...!”
Former Dark Cook C: “Yeah! So, please stay in this village and teach us your ways!”
Wandering Cook: “I'm a cook...”
Wandering Cook: “I have a purpose to fulfill.”
Girl: “Yeah, we know... You have to keep helping everyone that's in need of your cooking.”
Girl: “But promise me this...”
Girl: “If we ever need your cooking again, you have to come back and make food for us, okay...?”
Wandering Cook: “Okay, I promise.”
Narrator: “And so, the Wandering Cook resumed his journey to help those in need of good food.”
Narrator: “He would venture back into the wastes, but a figure kept watching over him. The girl as she awaited his return.”
Girl: “Goodbye, Mr. Cook.”
MC: That concludes all the presentations for the first annual Kamiyama High School Arts Festival.
An: Every class did such an amazing job! I really loved the dance routine Mizuki's class did!
Nene: Aoyagi looked like he had fun dancing too.
Tachibana: But everyone cheered like crazy when they saw our film. That means we did a pretty good job too, right?
Amisawa: Yeah! Do you think we have a shot at winning?!
An: Haha. I dunno about that. I mean, Kusanagi said it's gonna be hard for us to...
Nene: We might actually have a shot...
An: What?
Nene: To tell you the truth, I was worried sick this whole time...
Nene: I thought we did a good job since we worked really hard on it, but I still wasn't sure how others would react to it...
Soda: Kusanagi...
Nene: But I could see that everyone was enjoying it once they started watching it...
Nene: Including me. Once it started playing on the big screen...
Nene: I found myself also having fun!
Nene: When everyone first asked me to direct our film, I wasn't at all sure how I'd do...
Nene: I'm really shy... I also felt this wall between me and all of you guys.
Akito: You did?
Nene: Y-Yeah... But I got to know all of you as we worked on our film and became more comfortable as time went on.
Nene: And I'm really glad we did this.
Tachibana: Kusanagi...
An: Kusanagi!
Nene: Eep! Wh-Why are you shaking my hand...?
An: Hehe♪ What you just said makes me feel so happy!
An: So, thank you! Making that film with you was super duper fun!
Amisawa: Yeah, I also had a lot of fun! We should go fly drones together again sometime!
Tachibana: And you promised to go clothes shopping with me, remember?
Soda: You gotta stop by my dojo sometime! I wanna introduce our film's director to all the kids!
Nene: All of you...
Nene: Thanks.
Akito: Alright, you guys, settle down...
MC: Thank you all for being so patient. We have our tallies.
Nene: Oh...
Akito: It's time...
An: I hope we do well since we worked so hard on our film...!
MC: We'll get started right away by announcing our third-place winner. Class 2-B.
MC: With their interpretive dance titled “Alligator: Where Will The Waters Take Us?”
MC: Please send a representative up to the stage.
Toya: We did it, Akiyama...!
Mizuki: Yeah! It was really tough conceptually, but I'm glad we worked so hard on the costumes for it!
MC: Next, in second place comes... Class 1-A with their orchestral rendition of “A Sonata For You”.
Nene: Oh, that class with the orchestra...
Akito: They even roped in the music teacher. It's hard to believe some were playing their instruments for the first time...
An: Yeah, they definitely deserve a spot on the podium...!
Nene: (Which just leaves first place...)
Nene: (Maybe we never really had a shot. But...)
MC: Now, in first place. The winner of the first annual Kamiyama High School Arts Festival is...
MC: Class 3-C! With their play titled “The Phantom Of The Opera And The Tunnel To Another World”.
Tsukasa: Yeeeessss! We did it, Rui!
Rui: We really did. Thank you, Tsukasa, everyone... Our hard work paid off.
An: That's too bad...
Nene: Yeah... I really thought we had a chance too.
Nene: But not placing isn't the end of the world. To me, what we made means...
MC: Next, we have a special prize from our judge.
Nene: Huh...?
Akito: A special prize...?
An: Oh, our teacher did mention something about inviting a special guest to serve as the judge...
MC: We've specially invited screenwriter Mr. Heizaburo Taniyama to serve as our judge today. And his decision is in.
MC: Our special prize goes to... Class 2-A!
Nene: What...?
An: Whaaaat?!?!
Taniyama: To be honest, as a screenwriter, I wasn't sure how this class was going to keep the story in this film together. I was on the edge of my seat the entire time.
Taniyama: However, they ended up doing a wonderful job. And in every frame, I could tell that they really worked as a team to make this film happen.
Taniyama: I believe the tale of the Wandering Cook was an extraordinary expression of your youth... And I hereby award you with this prize. Congratulations.
Nene: Oh...
An: We did it, Kusanagi! We won the judge's prize!
Nene: Yeah... I'm so glad...!
MC: Will the representative for Class 2-A please come join us on the stage to accept this trophy.
Nene: The representative...?
Akito: Guess who, right?
An: Yup! Go on up, Kusanagi!
Nene: Huh? M-Me...?!
Tachibana: Go! You're the director!
Nene: O-Okay...
Taniyama: Congratulations on your fantastic film.
Nene: Th-Thank you very much.
Nene: (This trophy's heavier than I expected...)
Nene: (It's like I'm carrying everyone with me...)
Female Students: Over here, Director! We wanna take some pictures!
Male Students: Way to go, Director!
Nene: Y-You guys...
Nene: (I'm a bit different from them, and they're still really prone to getting excited over the littlest things...)
Nene: (But I'm so glad I agreed to become the director...)
Nene: (I hope we get to have more fun and keep doing stuff like this together.)
